<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62ae0499-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s2904"><num value="2904">§ 2904.</num><heading> No restrictions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The right of Native Americans to express themselves through the use of Native American languages shall not be restricted in any public proceeding, including publicly supported education programs.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id62ae049a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/477/tI/s105">Pub. L. 101–477, title I, § 105</ref>, <date date="1990-10-30">Oct. 30, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/1155">104 Stat. 1155</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
